<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="481" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1052,1079]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Iwasa, 2020" authorityName="Iwasa" authorityYear="2020" box="[475,601,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[475,601,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">C. yezoana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,699,1053,1079]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[609,699,1053,1079]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be recognized by blackish thorax and abdomen with greyish microtrichose, yellow legs, and surstylus not bifurcated apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="481" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,1124,1151]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[429,513,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,273,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[289,1297,273,1622]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Cordilura yezoana sp. nov., holotype. 28, male adult, left lateral view; 29, male sternite V; 30, male terminalia, left lateral view; 31, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701095/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
; 
<typeStatus box="[525,625,1125,1152]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">holotype</typeStatus>
). 
<emphasis box="[647,708,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Head</emphasis>
: eyes reddish brown; frons brownish yellow, eye margin brown; face and gena yellow; occiput dark brown; postpedicel black, basally yellow and approximately 2 times as long as wide; pedicel yellow; arista black and short-haired; palpus white, spatulate, and with comparatively weak subapical seta; proboscis yellow; vibrissal angle with 1 strong vibrissae and 1 subvibrissa. Chaetotaxy (black): 4 
<emphasis box="[1323,1342,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">fr</emphasis>
, 3 
<emphasis box="[1380,1405,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">or</emphasis>
(1 proclinate, 2 lateroclinate), 1 
<emphasis box="[481,509,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">vti</emphasis>
(strong), 1 
<emphasis box="[639,672,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">vte</emphasis>
(weak), 1 
<emphasis box="[792,818,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">oc</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[853,893,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">poc</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Thorax</emphasis>
: thin greyish microtrichose; scutum and scutellum black, proepisternum yellow in ventral half and black in dorsal half, with sparse long hairs; anepisternum, anepimeron and katatergite black; katepisternum ventrally yellow and dorsally black; meron brown; anatergite and metanotum black. Chaetotaxy: 2 
<emphasis box="[1170,1223,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pprn</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis box="[1260,1296,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">npl</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[1333,1430,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">prest iar</emphasis>
, 2+3 
<emphasis box="[202,228,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">dc</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis box="[263,288,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">sa</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis box="[323,351,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pa</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[386,423,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">dsc</emphasis>
(developed), 1 
<emphasis box="[599,650,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">apsc</emphasis>
(small), 1 
<emphasis box="[771,840,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">prepst</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis box="[875,946,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">prepm</emphasis>
, 1 strong and 2 weak anepst, 1 
<emphasis box="[1298,1343,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">kpst</emphasis>
. Wings: slightly tinged with brown; veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[559,585,1466,1480]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">4+5</subScript>
and M almost parallel; vein A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[939,947,1466,1480]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">1</subScript>
+CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1016,1024,1466,1480]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">2</subScript>
extending to wing margin; calypter yellow, with hairs marginally; halteres whitish yellow. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[836,914,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,273,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[289,1297,273,1622]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Cordilura yezoana sp. nov., holotype. 28, male adult, left lateral view; 29, male sternite V; 30, male terminalia, left lateral view; 31, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701095/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Fig 28</figureCitation>
): yellow; all femora with long hairs on ventral surface; fore tibia with 1 
<emphasis box="[441,469,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">ad</emphasis>
and 1 
<emphasis box="[549,577,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pd</emphasis>
near middle, and 3 preapicals; mid tibia with 2 
<emphasis box="[1128,1156,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">ad</emphasis>
near middle and 1 
<emphasis box="[1379,1407,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pd</emphasis>
at basal one-third and 1 
<emphasis box="[398,426,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pd</emphasis>
at distal one-third; hind tibia with 1 
<emphasis box="[845,873,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">ad</emphasis>
and 1 
<emphasis box="[951,979,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pd</emphasis>
at distal two-fifths and 1 
<emphasis box="[1273,1301,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">ad</emphasis>
and 1 
<emphasis box="[1380,1408,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">pd</emphasis>
at one-fifth, and 3–4 preapicals.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Abdomen</emphasis>
: tergites black and thinly microtrichose, covered by short setulae and each tergite laterally and posteriorly with comparatively long setae; sternite IV round quadrangle; sternite V (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1179,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,273,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[289,1297,273,1622]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Cordilura yezoana sp. nov., holotype. 28, male adult, left lateral view; 29, male sternite V; 30, male terminalia, left lateral view; 31, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701095/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) prominently bilobate (brown) posteriorly, covered by hairs; epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[712,838,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,273,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[289,1297,273,1622]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Cordilura yezoana sp. nov., holotype. 28, male adult, left lateral view; 29, male sternite V; 30, male terminalia, left lateral view; 31, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701095/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Figs 30, 31</figureCitation>
) well developed, covered by setulae and with several pairs of distinct setae posterioly; surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[637,765,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,273,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[289,1297,273,1622]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Cordilura yezoana sp. nov., holotype. 28, male adult, left lateral view; 29, male sternite V; 30, male terminalia, left lateral view; 31, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701095/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Figs 30, 31</figureCitation>
) slender and pigmented, and both close each other apically; cercal plate covered by setulae, with a pair of long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" box="[199,635,1808,1835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,292,1809,1835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Length.</emphasis>
Body, 7.0 mm; wing, 
<quantity box="[542,631,1808,1835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" box="[199,418,1845,1871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1845,1871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,560,1880,1908]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" box="[199,560,1880,1908]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1880,1907]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,423,1881,1907]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[438,552,1881,1908]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="481" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,980,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1917,1943]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after former given name of locality (
<collectingRegion box="[994,1108,1917,1944]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
) where the 
<typeStatus box="[1238,1336,1917,1943]" pageId="10" pageNumber="481">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,251]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,153,179]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ozerov, 2007" authorityName="Ozerov" authorityYear="2007" box="[604,994,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tartariana">
<emphasis box="[604,837,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">Cordilura tartariana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ozerov, A. L." box="[843,994,153,179]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" pagination="123 - 126" refId="ref7060" refString="Ozerov, A. L. (2007) Four new species of dung flies (Diptera: Scathophagidae) from Russian Far East. Russian Entomological Journal, 16, 123 - 126." type="journal article" year="2007">
Ozerov, 
<quantity box="[938,994,153,179]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.097779999999999" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" unit="in" value="2007.0">2007</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in structure of male surstyli, but differs from it in the following characteristics: scutum black; katepisternum anteroventrally yellow and posterodorsally black; meron brown. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ozerov" authorityYear="2007" box="[421,569,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tartariana">
<emphasis box="[421,569,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">C. tartariana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, scutum yellowish; katepisternum and meron wholly yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
